Packages contain package.json file (describes the package) and the JS file
Supposed to do one thing really well
Use different packages together
Someone who wants to push a package that goes through the NPM registry
Downside: Not all packages are good code, but your project can also get messy and bigger
Yarn supposed to get packages from NPM registry
NPM stands for Node Package Manager

Three types of packages:
Used on the browser (jquery)
Give you new commands that's on the command line
Those used for Node.js (backend)
React is a package
(LTS stands for Long Term Support)

Three things to follow:

1. HTML + CSS + JavaScript
2. Github Repo + Git
3. Package.json file
